Script,BasicMajorBoth
window.currentPBSScenario = 'BasicMajorBoth';
window.currentPBSScenarioFilename = 'Basic_Major_Both';
console.log('PBS: Logging scenario selection for BasicMajorBoth');
fetch('https://bba.harmonicsystems.com/api/scenario/select', {
    method: 'POST',
    headers: {
        'Content-Type': 'application/json',
        'X-Client-Version': '1.0.0'
    },
    body: JSON.stringify({
        scenario: 'BasicMajorBoth',
        user: whoAmI() || 'anonymous'
    })
}).then(function(r){ console.log('PBS: Server response', r.status); }).catch(function(e){ console.log('PBS: Fetch error', e); });
setDealerCode(`

/*
convention-card-ns: Basic-Bridge
convention-card-ew: Basic-Bridge
auction-filter: Auction.....\n1[HS] +Pass +(1[SHN]|2N|[234][HS])
*/
# curate: kind=bidding
# convention-card-ns: Basic-Bridge
# convention-card-ew: Basic-Bridge


dealer south

# Opener predicate for a seat: 12-21 HCP with a 5+ card major.
sOpen = hcp(south) > 11 and hcp(south) < 22 and (spades(south) > 4 or hearts(south) > 4)
nOpen = hcp(north) > 11 and hcp(north) < 22 and (spades(north) > 4 or hearts(north) > 4)

# Responder predicate: 6-12 HCP, and NOT itself an opening 5-major hand
# (so each deal has exactly one opener — the auction stays clean).
sResp = hcp(south) > 5 and hcp(south) < 13 and not (hcp(south) > 11 and (spades(south) > 4 or hearts(south) > 4))
nResp = hcp(north) > 5 and hcp(north) < 13 and not (hcp(north) > 11 and (spades(north) > 4 or hearts(north) > 4))

# Quiet opponents
eHcp = hcp(east) < 11
wHcp = hcp(west) < 11

# Either South opens and North responds, OR North opens and South responds.
((sOpen and nResp) or (nOpen and sResp)) and eHcp and wHcp

action printoneline,
average "South opens (you)   " 100 * (hcp(south) > 11 and (spades(south) > 4 or hearts(south) > 4)),
average "North opens (partner)" 100 * (hcp(north) > 11 and (spades(north) > 4 or hearts(north) > 4)),
average "South HCP avg "       hcp(south),
average "North HCP avg "       hcp(north),
`, "S", true)
Script
Button,Basic 1M (both seats),\n\
--- Basic 1M — both seats (beginner)\n\
A 1-of-a-major auction. On some deals YOU (South) open 1!H/1!S and choose\n\
your rebid; on others partner (North) opens and YOU respond. Either way,\n\
make the right call from your seat.\n\
\n\
When you OPEN (12-21 HCP，5+ in a major): open your major，then rebid to\n\
describe your strength and shape on the next round.\n\
\n\
When you RESPOND to partner's 1!H/1!S:\n\
• New suit (1!S over 1!H) — 6+ HCP，4+ cards，no fit\n\
• 1NT — 6+ HCP，no support，no biddable new suit\n\
• Simple raise (2M) — 6-9 HCP with 3+ support\n\
• Limit raise (3M) — 10-12 HCP with 4+ support\n\
• 2NT — 11-12 balanced (Jacoby 2NT in some systems — see chart)\n\
• Game raise (4M) — preemptive with 5+ support\n\
\n\
For beginners: count HCP，count support，choose the call your seat calls for.\n\
\n\
Reference: https://www.bridgebum.com/responses_to_one_of_a_major.php\n\
%BasicMajorBoth%
